<title>UK: U.S. stocks weak in London, tobacco shares weigh.</title>
<headline>U.S. stocks weak in London, tobacco shares weigh.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Most U.S. stocks were weaker in London on Monday, dragged down by tobacco shares in the wake of the U.S. industry settlement.</p>
<p>Shares in Philip Morris Cos Inc were trading down $7/8 in London to $44-3/4, while shares in RJR Nabisco Holdings Corp were off $1/2 to $34.</p>
<p>Dealers characterised the drop as a knee-jerk reaction to the $368.5 billion settlement reached on Friday. It was complicated by recent moves by the U.S. government to raise cigarette taxes.</p>
